*soya-0.14 (07 Dec 2008)

  07 Dec 2008; Patrick Lauer <patrick@gentoo.org> +soya-0.14.ebuild:
  Bumping to 0.14. Closes 184510. OpenAL is no longer optional even though
  the configure script checks for that, so the useflag is removed for now

  06 Aug 2008; Jesus Rivero <neurogeek@gentoo.org> metadata.xml,
  soya-0.10.2.ebuild:
  add GLEP 56 USE flag desc from use.local.desc. Fixed ebuild minorsyn
  reported by repoman

  28 Jan 2007; Tiziano Müller <dev-zero@gentoo.org> soya-0.10.2.ebuild:
  Removed insopts-line for tutorial (bug #164166).

*soya-0.13_rc1 (28 Jan 2007)

  28 Jan 2007; Tiziano Müller <dev-zero@gentoo.org> +soya-0.13_rc1.ebuild:
  Version bump (bug #132067), fixes bug #164166 as well.

  16 Jul 2006; Alastair Tse <liquidx@gentoo.org> -soya-0.9.1.ebuild,
  -soya-0.9.2.ebuild, -soya-0.10.ebuild, -soya-0.10.1.ebuild:
  cleanups

  13 Jun 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> soya-0.10.2.ebuild:
  Stable on x86 since this was the version I tested with the new
  slune/openal/freealut.

